Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

## 1. Windows-Only Tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[SupportedOSPlatform("windows")]
// Or use a condition:
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ... registry code
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI - requires local GPU");
    // ... GPU code
}
```

Then exclude in CI with: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky External API — Retry

MSTest v3+ has built-in retry:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // Retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task WeatherApiTest()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Even on Failure

Use `[TestCleanup]` — it runs after every test regardless of pass/fail:

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestMethod]
public void FileProcessingTest()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "test data");
    // ... assertions
}

[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}
```

Or use `try/finally` inline for single-test scoping:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void FileTest()
{
    var temp = Path.GetTempFileName();
    try
    {
        // ... test logic and assertions
    }
    finally
    {
        File.Delete(temp);
    }
}
```

---

**Summary of key attributes:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + `[TestCategory]` |
| Skip in CI | Environment check + filter on `--filter` |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally` |
